The paper discusses distributed optimization in machine learning, which is a common topic in the cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-category. The use of mobile devices as compute nodes also suggests a potential fit for the cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) sub-category. The uneven distribution of data and the need for communication efficiency may also make this paper relevant to the cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) sub-category. The focus on optimization and updating a global model could also fall under the cs.SY (Systems and Control) sub-category. Finally, the use of machine learning for on-device intelligence could potentially place this paper in the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-category.
